f `checkCoeffDvd` is `true`, then when using a polynomial `k*m - p`\nto simplify `.. + k'*m*m_2 + ...`, the substitution is performed IF\n- `k` divides `k'`, OR\n- Ring implements `NoNatZeroDivisors`.\n\nWe need this check when simplifying disequalities. In this case, if we perform\nthe simplification anyway, we may end up with a proof that `k * q = 0`, but\nwe cannot deduce `q = 0` since the ring does not implement `NoNatZeroDivisors`\nSee comment at `PolyDerivation`.\n","docLink":"./Lean/Meta/Tactic/Grind/Arith/CommRing/RingM.html#Lean.Meta.Grind.Arith.CommRing.RingM.Context.checkCoeffDvd","kind":"def","line":43,"name":"Lean.Meta.Grind.Arith.CommRing.RingM.Context.checkCoeffDvd","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b4812ae53eea93439ad5dce5a5c26591c31cb697/src/Lean/Meta/Tactic/Grind/Arith/CommRing/RingM.lean#L43-L43"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Meta/Tactic/Grind/Arith/CommRing/RingM.html#Lean.Meta.Grind.Arith.CommRing.RingM.Context.ringId\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Meta</span>.<span class=\"name\">Grind</span>.<span class=\"name\">Arith</span>.<span class=\"name\">CommRing</span>.<span class=\"name\">RingM</span>.<span class=\"name\">Context</span>.<span class=\"name\">ringId</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">self</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Meta/Tactic/Grind/Arith/CommRing/RingM.html#Lean.Meta.Grind.Arith.CommRing.RingM.Context\">Context</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">Nat</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Lean/Meta/Tactic/Grind/Arith/CommRing/RingM.html#Lean.Meta.Grind.Arith.CommRing.RingM.Context.ringId","kind":"def","line":31,"name":"Lean.Meta.Grind.Arith.CommRing.RingM.Context.ringId","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b4812ae53eea9343